! only meal would be after None (at 3pm)
Room Refectory "Refectory"
  with
    description
      "The refectory is a long, austere hall where the community takes its
        meals in silence while one brother reads aloud from the lectern. Two
        rows of trestle tables stretch the length of the room, their worn oak
        surfaces scrubbed clean. High windows along the eastern wall admit thin
        shafts of light that barely reach the stone floor. The smell of
        pottage lingers faintly in the air. A doorway to the
        south leads to the kitchen, and wide openings to the north return to
        the cloister.",
    e_to CloisterSE,
    n_to CloisterN,
    s_to TODO_AREA,
    ! s_to Kitchen,
  ;

